     Pick The Next Cable Colour →
  • You can resize the app by resizing your browser window or pinch-zoom on mobile and tablet devices.
  • Choose a cable colour, click/tap a patch point, then click/tap a destination patch point to set a cable. Double-click/tap it to remove it.
  • Use the small grey circular handles, located half-way along the cable, to alter the shape of the cable arc. Click and drag to move them.
  • It is possible to have multiple cables in one patch point.
  • Clicking the pedal jacks will indicate that a pedal should be plugged in.
  • Click and drag a control knob or fader, and click buttons & toggle switches to mimic the positions on your actual Matriarch.
  • Saving the patch will save a .json file with the name given in the 'Patch Name' field directly to your downloads folder. You can then use this file to reload the patch into the app at a later date.
  • In the same manner, exporting a PNG will save a png snapshot of the current app state, including the patch name and notes, with dimensions: 3440x1920 (App native).
  • A colour slider for the control position indicators is available to help people who see colours differently. Set it to change the hue. (This is unavailable on Safari, due to restrictions of how it applies filters.)

Enjoy!
